body_html: I did the implementation for nearest neighbor in #588 (funny enough, blame doesn't show me anymore). That algorithm is good enough for my purposes and I've been using it since. So from my side, we can close this bug @girving. But there might be others that want fast implementations for other algorithms such as @TimZaman. Maybe I'll come around and do some benchmarking of the current implementation of bilinear and see what can be done. Who's the author of it?
